1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:01,400
[Disclaimer:
All depicted events are fictional

2
00:00:01,440 --> 00:00:02,600
and for entertainment purposes only;
viewer discretion is advised]

3
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:18,560
[Love Upon a Time Series]

4
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:20,320
Thee?!

5
00:00:20,450 --> 00:00:21,340
Pun!

6
00:00:21,370 --> 00:00:22,950
Yes. I'm safe now.

7
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Klao...

8
00:00:24,130 --> 00:00:25,920
Jom's words were true.
You have lost your wits.

9
00:00:26,010 --> 00:00:27,420
Who were those two?

10
00:00:27,530 --> 00:00:28,640
Jom and Kaew,

11
00:00:28,680 --> 00:00:30,600
companions since our youth.

12
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:31,930
Dearest Klao,

13
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:33,720
my name is Lady Prayong,

14
00:00:33,830 --> 00:00:35,150
Lord Phop's mother.

15
00:00:35,180 --> 00:00:37,650
On the morrow, we shall visit the temple.

16
00:00:37,820 --> 00:00:39,530
Kindly join me on this journey.

17
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:46,700
Lord Preechapiban.

18
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:50,600
Will you confess to your misdeeds?

19
00:00:54,040 --> 00:00:56,480
The Legal Principles decree that

20
00:00:56,880 --> 00:01:00,630
whosoever is found guilty of bribery,

21
00:01:01,010 --> 00:01:02,710
or of engaging in corruption,

22
00:01:03,590 --> 00:01:05,710
such as the trafficking of opium,

23
00:01:06,420 --> 00:01:10,130
shall receive fifty lashes
upon the back,

24
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:12,450
be subjected to a fourfold fine,

25
00:01:12,510 --> 00:01:15,630
and condemned to a life of servitude.

26
00:01:20,890 --> 00:01:22,380
My father is innocent.

27
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:24,240
Be not so hasty in your judgment.

28
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:27,270
He is indeed guiltless.

29
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:28,640
Cease this, son.

30
00:01:30,910 --> 00:01:32,440
If you are indeed innocent,

31
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:35,509
why do you remain so silent?

32
00:01:36,550 --> 00:01:38,580
Speak the truth, Father.

33
00:01:39,340 --> 00:01:41,259
Quite an audacious tongue you possess.

34
00:01:43,460 --> 00:01:44,990
Refrain from this outburst,

35
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:49,759
or the lash shall find you
as it did your father, Lord Preechapiban.

36
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:54,640
Bear this burden in silence for now,

37
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:57,840
for the day shall come

38
00:01:58,880 --> 00:02:00,400
when the truth is laid bare before all.

39
00:02:01,590 --> 00:02:02,980
Escort him out.

40
00:02:22,300 --> 00:02:23,200
Father...

41
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:24,570
Father.

42
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,160
Father!

43
00:02:28,620 --> 00:02:29,460
Father!!

44
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:36,120
Father!

45
00:02:36,550 --> 00:02:37,120
Father!!

46
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:39,480
Father is no more, Master!

47
00:02:48,730 --> 00:02:50,020
Master Klao...

48
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:51,820
Haunted by a nightmare, Master?

49
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:53,610
This dream again.

50
00:02:54,250 --> 00:02:56,350
Was Klao's father a convict?

51
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:58,820
Right. Back then...

52
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:00,710
Don't!

53
00:03:01,340 --> 00:03:02,390
Scum. You son of a rogue!

54
00:03:02,410 --> 00:03:04,960
- Vile thing!
- You shall never prosper, Klao!

55
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:06,120
Prior to his passing,

56
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:07,550
Lord Preechapiban,

57
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:09,280
your father,

58
00:03:09,770 --> 00:03:11,150
left you in my keeping.

59
00:03:13,270 --> 00:03:14,790
Klao's father is dead.

60
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:20,820
Dear me, Master.

61
00:03:21,890 --> 00:03:23,450
Did your father
appear in your dreams again?

62
00:03:24,090 --> 00:03:25,600
Klao's father...

63
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,079
I mean, my father...

64
00:03:28,390 --> 00:03:30,120
What was the cause of his death?

65
00:03:35,050 --> 00:03:35,960
Chuay.

66
00:03:36,640 --> 00:03:38,320
Can you please tell me about it?

67
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,190
Even this,

68
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:43,520
you have no recollection of, Master?

69
00:03:50,380 --> 00:03:51,720
Dawn is upon us, Master.

70
00:03:51,980 --> 00:03:55,030
Pray, go and freshen yourself.
We must prepare to go make merit.

71
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:56,920
Let us not speak of
such grim matters at this hour.

72
00:04:00,290 --> 00:04:01,880
What does it mean to be lashed?

73
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:08,640
Is it like being slashed
by a sword or a spear?

74
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:11,160
If that's the case,

75
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:13,880
it's fatal, isn't it?

76
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:18,440
Was my father a convict?

77
00:04:21,589 --> 00:04:24,600
Did he really do it?

78
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:27,590
Chuay, please tell me.

79
00:04:27,970 --> 00:04:29,150
I want to remember it.

80
00:04:30,640 --> 00:04:31,680
Master Klao.

81
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:35,080
Some matters...

82
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,250
are best left in the shadows.

83
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:44,730
I shall ready a cloth

84
00:04:44,990 --> 00:04:46,810
for your bath, Master.

85
00:04:58,820 --> 00:04:59,520
That...

86
00:05:01,710 --> 00:05:03,560
I think that wasn't just a dream,

87
00:05:05,330 --> 00:05:06,240
but rather

88
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:09,280
Klao's memories.

89
00:05:14,120 --> 00:05:16,270
[Love Upon a Time Series]

90
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:29,960
[Love Upon a Time Series]

91
00:07:01,810 --> 00:07:04,170
Chuay, can you heat up the water
like you did

92
00:07:04,210 --> 00:07:06,460
back at the small manor?

93
00:07:07,180 --> 00:07:09,380
I cannot, Master.
This manor is not ours.

94
00:07:10,050 --> 00:07:10,780
Klao.

95
00:07:12,340 --> 00:07:13,710
Make haste and take your bath.

96
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,700
We must shortly depart for the temple
with my mother.

97
00:07:19,020 --> 00:07:20,300
Well...

98
00:07:20,580 --> 00:07:21,980
If I...

99
00:07:23,020 --> 00:07:24,260
Like...

100
00:07:25,620 --> 00:07:26,860
It's too cold for me.

101
00:07:31,220 --> 00:07:32,900
The canal water
is warmer than that in a jar.

102
00:07:33,650 --> 00:07:35,570
Disrobe and bathe at once.

103
00:08:09,780 --> 00:08:11,300
What causes your hesitation?

104
00:08:12,460 --> 00:08:13,540
Are you mortified to bathe with me?

105
00:08:13,830 --> 00:08:15,710
Does "mortified" mean embarrassed?

106
00:08:15,740 --> 00:08:17,000
I'm not, of course!

107
00:08:21,050 --> 00:08:21,900
Out of the way.

108
00:08:22,580 --> 00:08:23,660
Like an eagle soaring on the wind!

109
00:08:33,299 --> 00:08:34,500
Don't touch me.

110
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:36,940
What have you to be shy about?

111
00:08:37,289 --> 00:08:38,470
I'm not shy.

112
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:40,470
I don't like making physical contact
when it's cold.

113
00:08:40,510 --> 00:08:41,360
Stop it!

114
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:44,080
Take off your clothes at once.

115
00:08:54,180 --> 00:08:55,270
Dear Klao.

116
00:08:55,590 --> 00:08:57,840
You appear as vibrant and full of life

117
00:08:58,510 --> 00:09:00,000
as you did before your journey to Phichit.

118
00:09:01,010 --> 00:09:04,050
Phichit? Did Klao ever move to Phichit?

119
00:09:05,190 --> 00:09:07,320
Does this manor afford you restful sleep?

120
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:09,470
I slept...nice and tight.

121
00:09:12,870 --> 00:09:14,080
What is it that makes you so tight?

122
00:09:17,130 --> 00:09:18,120
Chuay.

123
00:09:18,170 --> 00:09:18,900
Yes, my Lady?

124
00:09:19,260 --> 00:09:21,280
In what manner did you dress him,

125
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:23,000
that he should cry "tight" aloud?

126
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,110
See to his attire.

127
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:29,000
Yet I have attired him perfectly, my Lady.

128
00:09:31,380 --> 00:09:33,600
Nevertheless, I shall see to it.

129
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:36,440
- Hey, no need. It's okay.
- No, Master.

130
00:09:36,590 --> 00:09:38,400
- I can do it myself.
- As my Lady commands.

131
00:09:39,740 --> 00:09:40,880
Oh, Sai.

132
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,200
Yes, my Lady?

133
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:43,540
Kong.

134
00:09:43,700 --> 00:09:46,830
Ready the offerings
for the Buddha and the monks

135
00:09:46,910 --> 00:09:49,080
upon the boat at once.

136
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,300
Yes, my Lady.

137
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:04,560
My Lady,

138
00:10:05,610 --> 00:10:07,470
I beg your permission
to offer her my hand.

139
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,960
Kong is rather feeble.

140
00:10:10,030 --> 00:10:11,760
I fear for our timely departure.

141
00:10:12,140 --> 00:10:13,760
Kong is but feeble?

142
00:10:17,650 --> 00:10:19,620
If it be envy,

143
00:10:20,260 --> 00:10:21,640
then begone with all haste.

144
00:10:22,970 --> 00:10:23,720
Yes, my Lady.

145
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,520
What is it that you find tight?

146
00:10:33,470 --> 00:10:34,870
Allow me to adjust it.

147
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:35,920
Uh...

148
00:10:36,410 --> 00:10:37,920
It's not tight.

149
00:10:38,750 --> 00:10:40,120
Uh...

150
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,360
I spoke in the Phichit tongue,

151
00:10:43,820 --> 00:10:44,800
my Lady.

152
00:10:45,410 --> 00:10:46,090
Tight

153
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,220
means nice and cozy.

154
00:10:48,480 --> 00:10:51,260
I wanted to keep it short, my Lady.

155
00:10:54,390 --> 00:10:55,860
How endearing.

156
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,320
Let us set forth.

157
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:01,280
The rower shall soon arrive.

158
00:11:21,420 --> 00:11:22,620
Let us depart.

159
00:11:23,870 --> 00:11:24,650
Tightly.

160
00:11:46,930 --> 00:11:47,930
Whoa...

161
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:50,690
Weren't the ancient temples in Ayutthaya
made of red bricks?

162
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:54,520
Were they really this gorgeous
before the Fall of Ayutthaya?

163
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,880
What lingers in your thoughts?

164
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:02,120
Uh...

165
00:12:03,270 --> 00:12:04,080
Nothing.

166
00:12:04,430 --> 00:12:05,960
I just think that

167
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:08,960
this is quite a stunning temple...

168
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:10,920
uh... my Lord.

169
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:14,080
You must still retain some of the memories.

170
00:12:15,810 --> 00:12:17,230
Lord Preechapiban,

171
00:12:17,410 --> 00:12:18,800
your father,

172
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:22,520
and I once brought
Phop and you to a revel here.

173
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:25,040
Uh...

174
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:26,700
Auntie...

175
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:30,070
Forgive me, my Lady...

176
00:12:31,610 --> 00:12:35,360
were you an acquaintance of my father?

177
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:42,200
He suffers from amnesia.

178
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:48,400
I was more than a mere acquaintance of his.

179
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:54,960
Your father
was a companion of His Excellency.

180
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:57,530
This explains
your recurring visits to my manor,

181
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:59,680
and our travels in days gone by,

182
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:03,880
until...

183
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:07,800
your relocation to Phichit in his company,
when that incident occurred.

184
00:13:16,160 --> 00:13:18,040
Surely you miss him dearly.

185
00:13:18,900 --> 00:13:22,440
Now that we have come, let us pour water
to dedicate merit to his spirit.

186
00:13:27,190 --> 00:13:27,920
Yes.

187
00:13:52,580 --> 00:13:55,600
Pour water to dedicate merit
to the departed kinsfolk and companions.

188
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,530
Do you know how to proceed,

189
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,920
or has that too vanished
from your recollection?

190
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:29,020
Yatha varivaha pura

191
00:14:29,050 --> 00:14:31,680
paripurenti sagaram

192
00:14:31,710 --> 00:14:33,970
evameva ito dinnam

193
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:36,560
petanam upakappati.

194
00:14:36,580 --> 00:14:39,040
Icchitam patthitam tumham

195
00:14:39,070 --> 00:14:41,160
khippameva samijjhatu.

196
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:44,370
Sabbe purentu sankappa

197
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:47,130
cando pannaraso yatha.

198
00:14:47,170 --> 00:14:50,900
Mani jotiraso yatha.

199
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:54,810
Sabbitiyo vivajjantu

200
00:14:54,840 --> 00:14:57,840
sabbarogo vinas...

201
00:14:57,960 --> 00:15:01,520
Sabbitiyo vivajjantu

202
00:15:01,550 --> 00:15:04,680
sabbarogo vinassatu.

203
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:08,170
Ma te bhavatvantarayo

204
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:11,300
sukhi dighayuko bhava

205
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:14,050
abhivadanasilissa

206
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:17,100
niccam vuddhapacayino.

207
00:15:17,140 --> 00:15:20,670
Cattaro dhamma vaḍḍhanti

208
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:25,070
ayu vanno sukham balam.

209
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:43,520
Why am I

210
00:15:44,540 --> 00:15:45,760
actually sad?

211
00:15:47,010 --> 00:15:48,900
Klao's father isn't even mine.

212
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:51,960
Dearly me...

213
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:55,680
Has the ritual offered no comfort
to your troubled spirit?

214
00:15:56,920 --> 00:15:58,560
It pains me greatly to see you thus.

215
00:16:04,760 --> 00:16:06,000
Auntie...

216
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:08,870
My Lady,

217
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,160
I am...

218
00:16:11,380 --> 00:16:12,800
profoundly grateful to you.

219
00:16:15,790 --> 00:16:16,850
Dear Klao,

220
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:19,200
spare me the formalities.

221
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:22,000
Surely you have forgotten that

222
00:16:22,820 --> 00:16:24,840
your mother left this world
when you were still so young.

223
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:27,080
In days past,
you would follow me wherever I might go.

224
00:16:29,630 --> 00:16:31,040
It is true.

225
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:33,880
It was her you sought so dearly,

226
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:37,360
I fear you meant to claim her as your own.

227
00:16:39,170 --> 00:16:41,680
Do address me as "Aunt,"
as you did before, Dear Klao.

228
00:16:49,270 --> 00:16:50,270
Aunt.

229
00:16:52,780 --> 00:16:53,780
My father...

230
00:16:54,980 --> 00:16:58,680
Did he really commit a wrongdoing
and get executed?

231
00:17:06,280 --> 00:17:07,880
Ah! Stop!

232
00:17:08,069 --> 00:17:09,900
I beg of you! Please!

233
00:17:09,940 --> 00:17:12,470
I offer but a glimpse of the truth.

234
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:14,440
Who makes such a stir there?

235
00:17:15,319 --> 00:17:16,550
Here, at the outskirts of the temple…

236
00:17:16,579 --> 00:17:18,839
It could only be that strange oracle,
my Lady.

237
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:21,079
Phop,

238
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:22,480
grant them your aid.

239
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,819
- Understood.
- You wretched oracle!

240
00:17:24,849 --> 00:17:26,040
You stir discord between husband and wife.

241
00:17:30,740 --> 00:17:31,640
Chuay.

242
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:33,960
See to it that Klao
and my mother remain here.

243
00:17:47,310 --> 00:17:48,280
Dear Klao.

244
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:49,800
You vile, wicked wretch!

245
00:17:50,060 --> 00:17:51,800
How dare you speak thus?

246
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,680
If there is truly no other,

247
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:55,190
why this unrest?

248
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:56,880
This lady speaks the truth.

249
00:17:57,240 --> 00:17:59,640
If your heart
be free of such lustful desires,

250
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:02,000
why this sudden ferocious outburst?

251
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:04,000
- Curse you!
- You!!

252
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:05,630
What manner of business is this?

253
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:13,920
This wretched oracle has gone mad,

254
00:18:14,180 --> 00:18:16,560
for the prophecy delivered
is unsound and senseless,

255
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:18,800
turning my wife against me.

256
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:21,160
It is whispered in every corner.

257
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:22,840
I am entirely innocent, my Lord.

258
00:18:23,610 --> 00:18:26,220
I did but give voice to the prophecy.

259
00:18:30,950 --> 00:18:32,080
You are Dear Klao, are you not?

260
00:18:33,740 --> 00:18:34,750
You son of a rogue!

261
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:36,160
Return with another outburst?

262
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:37,680
It is he.

263
00:18:37,710 --> 00:18:38,550
- You son of a rogue.
- A man of unsound mind.

264
00:18:38,580 --> 00:18:39,580
What business have you here?

265
00:18:39,670 --> 00:18:42,170
- Why here? Another outburst?
- Indeed.

266
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:45,700
- You son of a rogue.
- Wretch.

267
00:18:47,570 --> 00:18:49,070
Return to your wretched dwelling.

268
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:51,650
Away with you! Return at once!

269
00:18:52,120 --> 00:18:53,280
You witless!

270
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:55,400
Ah!

271
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:56,640
Klao.

272
00:18:58,720 --> 00:18:59,610
Young man...

273
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:00,800
What troubles you so?

274
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:10,080
Fortune teller!

275
00:19:14,520 --> 00:19:15,880
It really is you.

276
00:19:17,150 --> 00:19:18,150
Recognize me and the hair?

277
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:20,080
Hair?

278
00:19:21,380 --> 00:19:22,920
My hair is as pristine as ever.

279
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:25,040
No, that's not what I meant.

280
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:26,680
It's me, Nakun,

281
00:19:27,130 --> 00:19:29,530
the guy who visited your pavilion
a few days ago.

282
00:19:29,830 --> 00:19:30,730
Pavilion?

283
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:36,960
Indeed.

284
00:19:38,240 --> 00:19:39,880
Once, I nearly became an oracle,

285
00:19:41,260 --> 00:19:43,920
serving the King at his pavilion.

286
00:19:46,840 --> 00:19:48,040
Cease this, Oracle.

287
00:19:48,380 --> 00:19:49,710
Stop this at once, Klao.

288
00:19:49,740 --> 00:19:51,280
You have caused a great disturbance.

289
00:19:52,940 --> 00:19:56,310
I am a lady,
though born in a man's guise.

290
00:19:57,070 --> 00:20:00,030
Thereafter, I was shunned and ill-treated.

291
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:03,080
My dream has crumbled to dust.

292
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:05,680
Stay out of this for now.

293
00:20:05,860 --> 00:20:07,280
Let me talk to her.

294
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:11,160
Please stop playing around.
It's me, Nakun...

295
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:20,120
Wrong place, wrong time,
and wrong circumstances.

296
00:20:20,950 --> 00:20:23,680
The promise and the wish

297
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:28,080
shall restore what was lost
and set wrongs aright!

298
00:20:47,460 --> 00:20:48,440
Young man.

299
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,440
Are you hungry?

300
00:20:58,910 --> 00:21:01,040
You know that
I traveled through time, don't you?

301
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:02,680
Klao, enough!

302
00:21:03,260 --> 00:21:04,160
Return to the manor.

303
00:21:04,470 --> 00:21:05,550
Oracle, take your leave now.

304
00:21:06,340 --> 00:21:07,240
Hey!

305
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:09,560
Don't leave just yet.

306
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:11,890
Let me talk to her, please.

307
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:13,200
Cease this at once, Klao.

308
00:21:19,550 --> 00:21:21,320
Pray, help us!

309
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:23,990
Ah! Giants have descended
upon the kingdom!

310
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:26,720
I, Sida, must now take my leave.

311
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:32,200
I must now take my leave.

312
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:37,480
Hey!

313
00:21:37,850 --> 00:21:40,200
I take the form of a golden deer

314
00:21:40,230 --> 00:21:42,960
and vanish into the wind.
- Oracle! Halt at once!

315
00:21:43,410 --> 00:21:44,150
Oracle!

316
00:21:44,190 --> 00:21:45,800
- I'm gone!
- Don't go, Fortune teller!

317
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:47,610
- Hey!
- Klao!

318
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:51,370
Is my meaning lost upon you?

319
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:52,280
Return to the manor!

320
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:53,480
I'm not heading back!

321
00:21:54,030 --> 00:21:56,080
I told you I wanted to talk to her first!

322
00:21:56,140 --> 00:21:58,760
Speaking with her
only draws you nearer to madness.

323
00:21:59,090 --> 00:22:00,160
Come with me.

324
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:04,520
Let go!

325
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:06,920
I shall let you go

326
00:22:07,110 --> 00:22:09,330
if you vow not to leave me.

327
00:22:11,760 --> 00:22:12,580
God!

328
00:22:13,120 --> 00:22:13,840
Hey!

329
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:18,200
Can you not be this much of a nuisance?

330
00:22:19,450 --> 00:22:20,480
I know you're worried about me.

331
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:23,280
I know we're childhood friends,

332
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:24,840
but we're grown-ups now.

333
00:22:25,160 --> 00:22:26,640
I can go wherever I want, can't I?

334
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:28,920
If we're really friends

335
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:30,440
and you care about me,

336
00:22:31,450 --> 00:22:32,450
give me some say in this.

337
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:35,360
My actions are for your sake.

338
00:22:37,280 --> 00:22:39,080
You ought not wander off
of your own accord,

339
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:43,400
for some ill-intentioned soul
seeks to do you harm.

340
00:22:46,030 --> 00:22:47,030
Do me harm?

341
00:22:52,180 --> 00:22:54,480
It is you who is harming me.

342
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:02,440
Forgive me.

343
00:23:05,420 --> 00:23:08,120
If caring means
watching over me like I'm a convict,

344
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:10,600
then you'd better stop.

345
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:12,200
It's uncomfortable.

346
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:41,080
May I speak with you at last?

347
00:23:44,800 --> 00:23:46,720
You have kept a sullen silence
the entire way back.

348
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:48,640
I won't talk.

349
00:23:49,160 --> 00:23:50,680
Don't disturb me either.

350
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:54,120
Master Klao! Master!

351
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:56,840
Master Klao.

352
00:24:01,900 --> 00:24:02,640
Phop.

353
00:24:04,740 --> 00:24:06,760
Perhaps you have been unduly harsh
with him.

354
00:24:07,080 --> 00:24:08,480
My concern was for his well-being.

355
00:24:10,540 --> 00:24:12,720
I once believed
the temple would afford him solace,

356
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:15,160
yet the presence of the masses

357
00:24:15,840 --> 00:24:17,760
has only deepened his derangement.

358
00:24:19,360 --> 00:24:21,600
Despite my many concerns for you,

359
00:24:22,540 --> 00:24:26,600
I have never constrained you.
Or have I been mistaken?

360
00:24:31,850 --> 00:24:33,750
The more you care and love,

361
00:24:34,030 --> 00:24:35,650
the kinder you must be.

362
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:39,680
You cannot simply force him
against his will.

363
00:24:58,510 --> 00:24:59,940
One moment he's sweet,

364
00:24:59,970 --> 00:25:01,280
the next he's fierce as a dog.

365
00:25:01,320 --> 00:25:02,740
He's got multiple personalities, or what?

366
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:05,160
No.

367
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:07,240
He's only got one personality:

368
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:09,760
being way too nosy about me!

369
00:25:13,900 --> 00:25:15,770
I want to go home already.

370
00:25:16,210 --> 00:25:17,600
If there are no starfalls,

371
00:25:17,740 --> 00:25:19,760
then what am I supposed to do?

372
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:24,360
Wrong time...

373
00:25:24,640 --> 00:25:25,560
Wrong place...

374
00:25:25,620 --> 00:25:26,560
Wrong circumstances...

375
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:28,680
Wrong time

376
00:25:29,230 --> 00:25:30,320
and wrong place.

377
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:35,000
She must've known
I traveled through time.

378
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:37,760
The promise

379
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:39,280
and the wish

380
00:25:39,700 --> 00:25:40,630
shall restore

381
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:43,520
what was lost and set wrongs aright.

382
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:47,060
What promise did you make, and to whom?

383
00:25:47,640 --> 00:25:49,170
Someone from the past
awaits its fulfillment.

384
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:53,200
What promise did Klao make, and to whom?

385
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:55,200
What did he fail to fulfill?

386
00:25:56,020 --> 00:25:58,800
Why didn't the fortune teller
make things easier for me?

387
00:26:05,980 --> 00:26:08,080
Did the professor
teach me anything about this?

388
00:26:20,540 --> 00:26:23,810
Just ask the student
who's sleeping...

389
00:26:23,860 --> 00:26:28,280
has he just traveled through time...

390
00:26:28,730 --> 00:26:31,720
and met what or whom?

391
00:26:33,080 --> 00:26:35,600
Gosh! Why must you fall asleep, Nakun?

392
00:26:36,350 --> 00:26:38,280
What else did she say?

393
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:46,000
It's to be able to adapt to
the settings of that era, isn't it?

394
00:26:46,040 --> 00:26:47,430
You're actually correct,

395
00:26:47,470 --> 00:26:49,270
but not entirely.

396
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:51,960
Ideally,

397
00:26:52,160 --> 00:26:54,160
we should give the main character

398
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:56,720
a mission or goal.

399
00:27:00,520 --> 00:27:01,170
What?

400
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:03,490
If you could go back in time,

401
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:05,280
what would your mission be?

402
00:27:08,260 --> 00:27:09,240
Don't know.

403
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:10,960
It might be...

404
00:27:11,720 --> 00:27:12,880
to get plenty of sleep

405
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:15,400
without being disturbed by you.

406
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:18,000
You look pretty worn out.

407
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:22,000
Wanna go to Gangnam Clinic with me
after the day's over

408
00:27:22,560 --> 00:27:23,920
and get some vitamins?

409
00:27:24,000 --> 00:27:24,840
Sounds nice.

410
00:27:25,120 --> 00:27:27,000
But can you let me doze off first?

411
00:27:27,400 --> 00:27:28,760
Stop talking to Thee, for God's sake.

412
00:27:29,340 --> 00:27:30,620
What did the professor say again?

413
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:35,760
Ideally,

414
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:38,010
we should give the main character

415
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:40,680
a mission or goal.

416
00:27:41,500 --> 00:27:42,240
For example,

417
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:45,280
the main character

418
00:27:45,470 --> 00:27:48,880
could travel back in time to alter history,

419
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:54,080
or solve a cold case in the past

420
00:27:54,320 --> 00:27:58,050
that then provides the key
to their investigation in the present.

421
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,600
Or the main character

422
00:28:01,170 --> 00:28:04,920
could travel back in time
to fall in love with someone

423
00:28:04,950 --> 00:28:08,130
they would never meet in the present.

424
00:28:08,950 --> 00:28:11,870
For the most part,
after accomplishing their mission,

425
00:28:11,900 --> 00:28:13,610
they'll learn

426
00:28:13,640 --> 00:28:15,800
and understand,
which leads to character development.

427
00:28:15,980 --> 00:28:16,960
At that moment,

428
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:20,520
the goal of time travel

429
00:28:21,920 --> 00:28:23,000
will be achieved.

430
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:25,600
Will the character return to the present?

431
00:28:27,340 --> 00:28:28,800
What an excellent question that was.

432
00:28:29,400 --> 00:28:30,200
Yes.

433
00:28:30,880 --> 00:28:33,480
It could be through a mirror,

434
00:28:34,840 --> 00:28:35,680
by drowning,

435
00:28:36,880 --> 00:28:39,740
or via a traditional Thai costume.

436
00:28:40,920 --> 00:28:41,720
However...

437
00:28:43,070 --> 00:28:47,150
should the main character
fail their mission,

438
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:51,320
the portal will be closed forever,

439
00:28:51,350 --> 00:28:54,760
preventing their return to their world.

440
00:28:58,520 --> 00:28:59,440
My mission!

441
00:29:13,310 --> 00:29:14,280
Chuay.

442
00:29:15,580 --> 00:29:16,440
Gosh.

443
00:29:17,290 --> 00:29:18,520
I'm sorry, Chuay.

444
00:29:19,550 --> 00:29:20,560
Think nothing of it, Master.

445
00:29:24,120 --> 00:29:26,960
Has your displeasure with Lord Phop
now come to an end?

446
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:28,960
Chuay, do you have

447
00:29:29,730 --> 00:29:31,400
a pencil or a pen?

448
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:33,720
A pencil, Master?

449
00:29:35,120 --> 00:29:37,000
Do you refer to the clay
meant for application to the face?

450
00:29:38,500 --> 00:29:39,800
No, not marl.

451
00:29:39,980 --> 00:29:42,690
A pen or a pencil, you know?

452
00:29:42,720 --> 00:29:43,720
A pen-seal, Master?

453
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:46,410
Oh, Master.

454
00:29:46,640 --> 00:29:48,000
Where am I to seek one?

455
00:29:48,060 --> 00:29:50,400
Might a duck or chicken pen
suffice in its stead?

456
00:29:56,160 --> 00:29:57,040
Go and get me one,

457
00:29:57,480 --> 00:29:58,760
or your lips will bleed.

458
00:30:05,690 --> 00:30:08,120
I'm telling you,
it's what's used for writing.

459
00:30:08,170 --> 00:30:11,560
It looks just like an ordinary pen,
like a quill with ink.

460
00:30:11,680 --> 00:30:13,460
A quill made from
a bird that cries "ka-ka-ka"?

461
00:30:13,490 --> 00:30:14,490
Yeah.

462
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:16,920
- That kind.
- "Ka-ka-ka-ka"?

463
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:17,920
Right?

464
00:30:19,680 --> 00:30:21,240
- You still don't get it?
- What is it used for?

465
00:30:21,290 --> 00:30:23,280
I told you it's for writing!

466
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:24,800
Writing, Master?

467
00:30:24,860 --> 00:30:26,000
Writing!

468
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:28,000
- In this manner?
- Yeah.

469
00:30:44,390 --> 00:30:45,280
Here, Master.

470
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:58,040
Chuay is unversed
in the use of scholarly instruments,

471
00:30:58,400 --> 00:31:00,760
unlike myself;
speak but one word, and I shall supply it.

472
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:04,310
Uh...

473
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:07,800
How does it work?

474
00:31:07,930 --> 00:31:09,280
Can you show me how it works?

475
00:31:11,380 --> 00:31:15,020
You are lettered, yet these instruments
are unfamiliar to you?

476
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:17,000
Do comply with his wishes.

477
00:31:17,260 --> 00:31:19,280
It is not ours to meddle in such matters.

478
00:31:24,370 --> 00:31:26,120
Behold, Master Klao.

479
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:28,160
Thus is it used.

480
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:30,240
- Oh...
- Do try it, Master.

481
00:31:31,800 --> 00:31:33,160
Back when...

482
00:31:34,800 --> 00:31:35,640
Uh...

483
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:37,440
I mean, in Phichit,

484
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:39,520
pens commonly used there

485
00:31:39,680 --> 00:31:41,000
come pre-filled with ink.

486
00:31:41,940 --> 00:31:45,400
It slowly comes out from the tip.

487
00:31:45,460 --> 00:31:46,740
No need to refill the ink.

488
00:31:52,470 --> 00:31:55,960
I wish to attend you to Phichit,
and behold its splendor with my own eyes.

489
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:58,030
Very well. Depart this place at once,

490
00:31:58,200 --> 00:31:59,260
and return not.

491
00:32:01,040 --> 00:32:01,840
Take your leave.

492
00:32:02,480 --> 00:32:04,220
- It is you who must leave.
- Take your leave.

493
00:32:04,250 --> 00:32:04,920
Take your leave, won't you?

494
00:32:05,080 --> 00:32:06,440
Go fight outside.

495
00:32:06,720 --> 00:32:07,960
I can't focus.

496
00:32:08,920 --> 00:32:10,510
Also, shut the door.

497
00:32:10,670 --> 00:32:11,750
The fault is yours.

498
00:32:11,980 --> 00:32:12,980
Yes, Master.

499
00:32:16,780 --> 00:32:18,190
Begone with all haste,
if such be your will.

500
00:32:18,230 --> 00:32:19,810
Your master was the one who drove us off.

501
00:32:19,870 --> 00:32:21,580
Since when have you become my master?

502
00:32:37,790 --> 00:32:41,400
My mission: Find out whatever happened
to the real Klao

503
00:32:52,800 --> 00:32:54,680
I told you not to come in yet, Chuay.

504
00:33:05,230 --> 00:33:07,960
Word from the kitchens reaches me
that you have remained here all day,

505
00:33:08,200 --> 00:33:10,000
neglecting even your meals.

506
00:33:12,480 --> 00:33:13,480
Well...

507
00:33:13,940 --> 00:33:16,480
I just want to finish my writing first.

508
00:33:17,060 --> 00:33:19,940
I am pleased that
you have resumed your scholarly pursuits,

509
00:33:20,020 --> 00:33:22,160
which is far preferable to indulgence.

510
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:25,880
- If you're forcing me to have dinner...
- No.

511
00:33:31,410 --> 00:33:33,030
I shall not oppose your wish to remain.

512
00:33:36,140 --> 00:33:37,420
I have brought this for you.

513
00:33:40,450 --> 00:33:43,460
Take some nourishment
before your stomach complains.

514
00:33:45,470 --> 00:33:47,650
It is of the finest quality,

515
00:33:49,810 --> 00:33:51,840
brought by traders from across China.

516
00:33:52,730 --> 00:33:55,060
Oranges are just 40 baht a kilo in Bangkok.

517
00:33:55,860 --> 00:33:57,500
What was it you spoke?

518
00:33:59,890 --> 00:34:01,880
Just leave the basket here. I...

519
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:03,440
I'll have them myself.

520
00:34:14,080 --> 00:34:15,500
Your hands are stained with ink.

521
00:34:16,949 --> 00:34:18,239
I shall prepare them for you.

522
00:34:22,570 --> 00:34:24,420
Why are the candles yet unlit at this hour?

523
00:34:26,510 --> 00:34:28,360
I would not have your eyes ache
as they did.

524
00:35:32,900 --> 00:35:34,080
Thanks.

525
00:35:36,700 --> 00:35:38,250
Forgive me for this morning.

526
00:35:42,020 --> 00:35:44,280
The fault was entirely mine
for pushing you.

527
00:35:46,230 --> 00:35:47,600
Do not hold it against me.

528
00:35:51,300 --> 00:35:52,230
Uh...

529
00:35:52,820 --> 00:35:54,770
I'd like to apologize as well.

530
00:35:55,930 --> 00:35:57,800
I was being rude to you.

531
00:36:00,520 --> 00:36:01,470
Why did you laugh?

532
00:36:03,730 --> 00:36:05,220
A slight stain of ink mars your face,

533
00:36:06,150 --> 00:36:08,320
like that of an aged and dirty feline.

534
00:36:11,560 --> 00:36:12,440
Here.

535
00:36:12,860 --> 00:36:14,400
I shall wipe it away.

536
00:36:17,080 --> 00:36:18,480
Uh... Well...

537
00:37:26,310 --> 00:37:27,310
Kong.

538
00:37:27,440 --> 00:37:29,640
To what purpose do you cast
your breath upon me, you bovine?

539
00:37:30,080 --> 00:37:32,070
It was you who turned towards me,

540
00:37:32,110 --> 00:37:33,310
you imbecile.

541
00:37:34,150 --> 00:37:35,480
Chuay! Kong!

542
00:37:39,310 --> 00:37:41,660
I entrusted him to your care,

543
00:37:42,270 --> 00:37:43,790
and yet you indulge in petty squabbles.

544
00:37:45,340 --> 00:37:48,150
Do you wish to be caned upon your back?

545
00:37:49,850 --> 00:37:50,990
No, my Lord.

546
00:37:51,030 --> 00:37:52,640
It shall not occur again, my Lord.

547
00:38:36,470 --> 00:38:37,890
I...

548
00:38:40,290 --> 00:38:41,520
shall take my leave now,

549
00:38:43,230 --> 00:38:46,070
that you may write with a clear mind.

550
00:38:47,250 --> 00:38:48,670
Alright. Oh...

551
00:38:49,970 --> 00:38:51,000
Yes, my Lord.

552
00:38:55,400 --> 00:38:57,200
Tarry not too long into the night, alright?

553
00:38:57,230 --> 00:39:01,000
♫Stay right here♫

554
00:39:01,030 --> 00:39:04,480
♫I shall spend the time I hold so dearly♫

555
00:39:04,510 --> 00:39:08,800
♫And make the most of it when I see you♫

556
00:39:08,830 --> 00:39:11,880
♫It makes my life so meaningful♫

557
00:39:11,910 --> 00:39:15,490
♫Simply stay right here♫

558
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:18,130
♫With those eyes I hold so dearly,♫

559
00:39:18,160 --> 00:39:21,010
♫I shall not falter♫

560
00:39:21,040 --> 00:39:26,530
♫With you by my side, we'll walk together♫

561
00:39:26,560 --> 00:39:28,840
♫Forever♫

562
00:39:36,720 --> 00:39:38,420
Perform such a massage
with your own hands,

563
00:39:38,850 --> 00:39:40,770
or have your servant assist you.

564
00:39:41,570 --> 00:39:43,280
It shall surely grant you tranquil slumber.

565
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:47,880
Kaew.

566
00:39:48,060 --> 00:39:49,620
Continue to massage him after me.

567
00:39:49,830 --> 00:39:51,010
Certainly.

568
00:39:58,530 --> 00:40:00,120
Avoid those of unsettled minds,

569
00:40:00,960 --> 00:40:01,960
for whatever they utter,

570
00:40:02,570 --> 00:40:04,180
Klao is apt to take as truth,

571
00:40:05,550 --> 00:40:07,200
and his condition shall only worsen,

572
00:40:07,650 --> 00:40:09,210
as though he were cursed.

573
00:40:11,940 --> 00:40:13,460
I see it the same way.

574
00:40:16,150 --> 00:40:18,010
However, do not merely confine him
within the manor.

575
00:40:18,790 --> 00:40:21,300
Even convicts in a prison
descend into madness,

576
00:40:22,310 --> 00:40:24,200
for they dwell only in shadows.

577
00:40:27,310 --> 00:40:28,310
To be concerned for his sake,

578
00:40:29,210 --> 00:40:30,810
one must do so with a measured heart.

579
00:40:33,170 --> 00:40:34,170
So nice...

580
00:40:34,980 --> 00:40:38,080
This feels like the spa
I visited in Ekkamai.

581
00:40:39,550 --> 00:40:40,960
What did you say?

582
00:40:41,840 --> 00:40:43,480
Oh, forget I said anything.

583
00:40:48,940 --> 00:40:52,440
Do you truly believe his present condition
arises from indulgence alone?

584
00:40:53,540 --> 00:40:56,880
If such were the cause, he should by now
have returned to his former self.

585
00:40:57,000 --> 00:40:58,600
I fear there is something deeper to this.

586
00:41:00,410 --> 00:41:01,410
Opium?

587
00:41:04,020 --> 00:41:05,330
I find it to be inconclusive.

588
00:41:07,640 --> 00:41:08,640
Now, tell me,

589
00:41:08,880 --> 00:41:11,240
have you discovered his whereabouts
during his absence?

590
00:41:17,100 --> 00:41:18,130
It seems not yet.

591
00:41:20,660 --> 00:41:22,780
To unveil his whereabouts

592
00:41:22,820 --> 00:41:25,100
shall enable us
to better discern his condition.

593
00:41:29,950 --> 00:41:32,080
This truly warms my heart, Klao.

594
00:41:32,420 --> 00:41:33,240
Hm?

595
00:41:33,550 --> 00:41:36,040
You speak with far greater reason.

596
00:41:38,050 --> 00:41:39,050
Uh...

597
00:41:39,340 --> 00:41:40,340
Well...

598
00:41:40,990 --> 00:41:43,810
It's probably due to the temple's grace

599
00:41:44,030 --> 00:41:46,520
and the merits I made for my father.

600
00:41:46,760 --> 00:41:48,280
That's why I feel a bit better.

601
00:41:48,540 --> 00:41:50,200
Have your memories of your father returned?

602
00:42:00,470 --> 00:42:01,470
Mm.

603
00:42:01,870 --> 00:42:02,870
Yes...

604
00:42:03,580 --> 00:42:04,580
I...

605
00:42:05,010 --> 00:42:06,940
I saw him at the court in my dream.

606
00:42:14,180 --> 00:42:16,260
It is known as the Court of Assessors.

607
00:42:17,840 --> 00:42:18,840
How wonderful.

608
00:42:19,240 --> 00:42:20,810
Do you recall your father?

609
00:42:22,890 --> 00:42:23,890
Uh...

610
00:42:24,500 --> 00:42:25,660
It is owing to Jom's practice.

611
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:27,170
I must hasten the massage.

612
00:42:27,580 --> 00:42:29,320
- Ow, ow.
- It is unnecessary.

613
00:42:32,310 --> 00:42:34,920
Only standard practice.
Let not your wit run ahead.

614
00:42:41,420 --> 00:42:42,540
In my dream,

615
00:42:43,760 --> 00:42:45,920
I saw my father

616
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:50,400
being sentenced to be slashed with a spear

617
00:42:52,790 --> 00:42:53,680
for

618
00:42:56,120 --> 00:42:57,040
his part...

619
00:42:58,230 --> 00:42:59,720
in corruption

620
00:43:00,170 --> 00:43:01,120
and bribery.

621
00:43:01,240 --> 00:43:02,840
With a spear?

622
00:43:10,420 --> 00:43:12,700
I heard it from the man,

623
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:14,960
whom I took for their leader,

624
00:43:17,460 --> 00:43:18,840
ordering that his back
be slashed with a spear.

625
00:43:20,520 --> 00:43:23,000
What he meant
was a lashing to his back.

626
00:43:28,680 --> 00:43:29,880
Lashing...

627
00:43:33,450 --> 00:43:34,400
with

628
00:43:36,260 --> 00:43:37,380
a rattan cane.

629
00:43:39,970 --> 00:43:42,280
What if my father was innocent?!

630
00:43:43,970 --> 00:43:45,820
I do believe your words.

631
00:43:47,850 --> 00:43:50,280
Lord Preechapiban is guiltless.

632
00:43:50,930 --> 00:43:52,270
The common folk

633
00:43:52,840 --> 00:43:55,040
remained in accord with the jury's verdict.

634
00:43:56,730 --> 00:43:58,800
Since your return to the capital,

635
00:43:59,260 --> 00:44:00,800
you have each night drifted

636
00:44:01,100 --> 00:44:03,120
toward indulgence in the market's corners.

637
00:44:04,480 --> 00:44:06,900
The sorrow you bear
must be beyond measure.

638
00:44:11,700 --> 00:44:12,910
I see now,

639
00:44:13,620 --> 00:44:14,890
from what I was told:

640
00:44:16,710 --> 00:44:18,800
some matters
are best left in the shadows.

641
00:44:24,910 --> 00:44:27,020
What a pitiable soul he is,

642
00:44:28,430 --> 00:44:31,060
having lost all memory of himself.

643
00:44:34,620 --> 00:44:35,680
Jom.

644
00:44:36,130 --> 00:44:39,440
What would you do
were I to lose all recollection of you?

645
00:44:41,090 --> 00:44:42,720
Nothing would need to be done.

646
00:44:46,080 --> 00:44:47,720
Utterly heartless.

647
00:44:49,170 --> 00:44:50,960
Nothing would need to be done,

648
00:44:51,820 --> 00:44:53,720
for my care would endure,

649
00:44:54,720 --> 00:44:56,520
even should you know me not.

650
00:45:09,410 --> 00:45:10,720
Jom...

651
00:45:12,270 --> 00:45:13,680
I am a physician.

652
00:45:14,150 --> 00:45:16,280
It is my duty to tend all who suffer,

653
00:45:17,970 --> 00:45:19,270
and you are no exception.

654
00:45:30,840 --> 00:45:33,560
Do you hold me in affection,

655
00:45:34,300 --> 00:45:36,160
or do you despise me,

656
00:45:36,930 --> 00:45:38,100
Jom?

657
00:45:51,970 --> 00:45:54,000
He brought up drinking at the market again.

658
00:45:54,680 --> 00:45:57,720
Is this why this deadpan-looking guy
doesn't like me visiting the market?

659
00:45:58,520 --> 00:45:59,440
Klao.

660
00:46:01,490 --> 00:46:04,240
Your father's affair has been settled.
Let it remain in the past.

661
00:46:05,480 --> 00:46:06,840
Cease your concern.

662
00:46:13,450 --> 00:46:15,010
Good heavens!

663
00:46:15,030 --> 00:46:17,800
Masters...

664
00:46:19,060 --> 00:46:22,960
A wallago of such remarkable size
was secured this day.

665
00:46:23,040 --> 00:46:25,440
Will you not take a taste?

666
00:46:27,610 --> 00:46:29,320
Oh, deary me!

667
00:46:30,490 --> 00:46:32,440
Spicy flavors
are not to Master Klao's taste,

668
00:46:33,070 --> 00:46:35,510
yet this contains no such heat.

669
00:46:40,350 --> 00:46:44,160
My dishes are of unique flavor,

670
00:46:44,190 --> 00:46:47,000
for I cook by no recipe.

671
00:47:09,420 --> 00:47:10,980
It is most true.

672
00:47:13,350 --> 00:47:14,880
Though the dishes lack heat,

673
00:47:15,840 --> 00:47:17,000
the excellence of their flavor endures.

674
00:47:22,260 --> 00:47:25,720
You flatter me far too much, Master.

675
00:47:38,650 --> 00:47:39,840
So clingy.

676
00:47:41,660 --> 00:47:42,320
Deary me.

677
00:47:42,460 --> 00:47:48,360
Were I to serve you spicy ant-larvae salad,
you would rejoice as though rich fortunes were yours.

678
00:47:48,860 --> 00:47:49,800
Egg...

679
00:47:50,430 --> 00:47:52,300
As for that dish,

680
00:47:53,250 --> 00:47:54,800
I shall decline, if it please you.

681
00:48:00,060 --> 00:48:01,140
So...

682
00:48:01,250 --> 00:48:03,250
Sorn, my beloved,

683
00:48:03,300 --> 00:48:06,920
once secured
a colossal weaver-ant nest with larvae.

684
00:48:07,150 --> 00:48:09,640
Naturally, I prepared
the spicy ant-larvae salad for my master,

685
00:48:10,090 --> 00:48:11,910
pouring all my heart into it,

686
00:48:11,950 --> 00:48:13,790
rushing about in haste,

687
00:48:14,190 --> 00:48:17,680
indulging in herbal spirits,

688
00:48:17,710 --> 00:48:20,120
and tending the child within me.

689
00:48:22,860 --> 00:48:23,960
So...

690
00:48:25,170 --> 00:48:26,120
it didn't turn out well?

691
00:48:26,240 --> 00:48:28,040
Oh! Absolutely flavorful!

692
00:48:28,080 --> 00:48:29,360
It was astonishing!

693
00:48:29,410 --> 00:48:32,520
One serving
could not possibly suffice to sate him.

694
00:48:33,460 --> 00:48:34,260
Huh?

695
00:48:35,430 --> 00:48:37,140
Then, my lips were bitten.

696
00:48:37,550 --> 00:48:38,560
Bitten?

697
00:48:39,770 --> 00:48:42,320
Can ant larvae even bite?

698
00:48:43,150 --> 00:48:44,920
Upon closer inspection,

699
00:48:45,370 --> 00:48:46,960
it seemed
I had been feasting upon termites.

700
00:48:59,520 --> 00:49:03,280
My lady scolded me with such fury
that one of us collapsed.

701
00:49:03,990 --> 00:49:05,530
Though it was she,

702
00:49:05,680 --> 00:49:08,760
for she had been reproaching me
for countless hours.

703
00:49:08,800 --> 00:49:13,360
Moreover, I was compelled
to dispose of the herbal spirits,

704
00:49:13,420 --> 00:49:15,760
and not long after,
she banished Sorn from the manor.

705
00:49:16,350 --> 00:49:17,550
You were guilty,

706
00:49:17,810 --> 00:49:19,930
so why was it Sorn

707
00:49:20,240 --> 00:49:21,520
who got punished instead?

708
00:49:22,040 --> 00:49:23,690
I always go by one belief:

709
00:49:23,720 --> 00:49:27,520
to shift every blame I incur onto others.

710
00:49:27,620 --> 00:49:29,880
It is far more comforting so.

711
00:49:42,280 --> 00:49:45,120
Aww! Master laughed with great joy.

712
00:49:45,680 --> 00:49:48,320
Would you care to partake
of the wallago curry,

713
00:49:48,670 --> 00:49:52,320
or the spicy ant-larvae salad
with termites?

714
00:50:18,080 --> 00:50:18,960
Tasty!

715
00:50:37,360 --> 00:50:38,440
What a delight.

716
00:50:38,710 --> 00:50:41,160
It has been so long
since I last witnessed your radiant smile.

717
00:50:41,660 --> 00:50:46,480
Well, a lot of things
have been keeping me from smiling.

718
00:50:46,610 --> 00:50:47,760
That said,

719
00:50:48,050 --> 00:50:50,440
it seems I must summon her
to converse with you each day.

720
00:50:50,850 --> 00:50:52,480
She's so much fun to talk to.

721
00:51:01,530 --> 00:51:02,660
Tomorrow...

722
00:51:03,360 --> 00:51:05,070
can I go to...

723
00:51:05,130 --> 00:51:07,640
the market with Muan?

724
00:51:07,900 --> 00:51:08,790
Like...

725
00:51:08,900 --> 00:51:10,690
Maybe it'll put me in a better mood

726
00:51:10,760 --> 00:51:13,180
and bring back some memories.

727
00:51:18,940 --> 00:51:20,560
I would grant it,

728
00:51:21,510 --> 00:51:22,920
were it not so dangerous there.

729
00:51:23,310 --> 00:51:24,450
Dangerous again?

730
00:51:25,690 --> 00:51:27,290
What's the deal with the market?

731
00:51:27,320 --> 00:51:29,260
Why do you keep telling me that
it's dangerous there?

732
00:51:33,000 --> 00:51:34,280
It's okay if you can't answer me.

733
00:51:35,060 --> 00:51:36,830
If it's that dangerous,

734
00:51:37,120 --> 00:51:38,400
go with me.

735
00:51:38,890 --> 00:51:40,480
This way, you can protect me.

736
00:51:48,970 --> 00:51:49,970
Please.

737
00:51:54,020 --> 00:51:55,800
Please, my Phop.

738
00:51:56,970 --> 00:51:58,320
Please...

739
00:51:59,230 --> 00:52:00,320
You...

740
00:52:01,620 --> 00:52:03,060
By what title did you just address me?

741
00:52:03,730 --> 00:52:04,720
My Phop.

742
00:52:05,350 --> 00:52:08,080
Please, take me there, my Phop.

743
00:52:15,030 --> 00:52:16,420
Were I not bound to patrol,

744
00:52:17,430 --> 00:52:19,040
I would take you there.

745
00:52:19,360 --> 00:52:20,000
Yes!

746
00:52:20,080 --> 00:52:23,880
You promised! Thank you!

747
00:52:37,300 --> 00:52:38,760
Thank you so much.

748
00:53:15,040 --> 00:53:16,120
Move!

749
00:53:16,690 --> 00:53:17,720
Forward!

750
00:53:18,200 --> 00:53:19,240
Move!!

751
00:53:33,740 --> 00:53:35,400
Lord Preechapiban.

752
00:53:35,950 --> 00:53:38,600
Will you confess to your misdeeds?

753
00:53:39,620 --> 00:53:41,480
Your punishment shall be mitigated,

754
00:53:41,840 --> 00:53:43,800
lightened to mere captivity.

755
00:53:48,880 --> 00:53:49,760
No.

756
00:53:51,480 --> 00:53:53,040
I did not commit the misdeeds.

757
00:53:54,280 --> 00:53:56,320
Why, then, must I confess?

758
00:53:59,850 --> 00:54:00,880
Two rounds

759
00:54:01,620 --> 00:54:02,840
of the lash.

760
00:54:05,800 --> 00:54:06,840
Father!!

761
00:54:09,090 --> 00:54:09,960
Klao!

762
00:54:22,760 --> 00:54:23,640
Father!!

763
00:54:35,440 --> 00:54:36,680
Klao's father was innocent,

764
00:54:36,910 --> 00:54:38,560
but he still got punished.

765
00:54:40,130 --> 00:54:40,960
Klao.

766
00:54:41,690 --> 00:54:44,000
Your heart was so broken
that you went drinking at the market.

767
00:54:44,880 --> 00:54:45,680
Or...

768
00:54:46,180 --> 00:54:47,720
is there something else to this?

769
00:55:04,760 --> 00:55:05,680
Sai.

770
00:55:06,160 --> 00:55:07,800
Do you take pleasure in feeding the fish?

771
00:55:08,470 --> 00:55:10,440
I take more pleasure in feeding you.

772
00:55:12,500 --> 00:55:14,610
- You do never cease to amaze me.
- Chuay.

773
00:55:15,510 --> 00:55:16,110
Yes, Master?

774
00:55:16,160 --> 00:55:17,320
Where is Phop?

775
00:55:17,440 --> 00:55:20,240
The Lord was summoned to his post
with utmost haste at dawn.

776
00:55:21,710 --> 00:55:25,520
When I stay home doing nothing,
he does nothing but watch over me.

777
00:55:25,930 --> 00:55:29,000
And he went on duty
the moment we made our promise.

778
00:55:30,290 --> 00:55:32,120
Is there a matter
you wish to discuss with him?

779
00:55:32,950 --> 00:55:33,800
No, there isn't.

780
00:55:34,680 --> 00:55:36,520
I just want to visit the capital.

781
00:55:36,990 --> 00:55:38,960
Have you sought his permission, Master?

782
00:55:40,260 --> 00:55:41,720
Uh...

783
00:55:42,130 --> 00:55:42,960
Yes.

784
00:55:43,460 --> 00:55:45,760
I discussed it with him last night.

785
00:55:48,110 --> 00:55:49,320
He lets me go there.

786
00:55:51,120 --> 00:55:52,420
Uh...

787
00:55:52,990 --> 00:55:56,480
Might I suggest that
you remain here until he returns, Master?

788
00:55:58,170 --> 00:56:01,120
It'll already be too late
by the time he returns.

789
00:56:01,430 --> 00:56:03,860
If such be the case, it is best
that you venture there on the morrow.

790
00:56:05,080 --> 00:56:05,980
Chuay.

791
00:56:09,200 --> 00:56:10,800
I'm so lonely I could die here.

792
00:56:11,800 --> 00:56:12,800
I've been staying in the manor,

793
00:56:13,470 --> 00:56:14,640
cut off from the light of day

794
00:56:15,250 --> 00:56:16,400
and from life itself.

795
00:56:17,710 --> 00:56:19,320
Why don't you feel sorry for me, Chuay?

796
00:56:20,080 --> 00:56:21,760
Didn't you say

797
00:56:22,320 --> 00:56:23,600
you loved me

798
00:56:24,840 --> 00:56:26,760
and were loyal to me?

799
00:56:39,440 --> 00:56:41,160
- Master.
- Gosh...

800
00:56:42,280 --> 00:56:43,560
Forgive me, I beg of you.

801
00:56:43,720 --> 00:56:45,150
Should you wish to enter the capital,

802
00:56:45,240 --> 00:56:46,840
I shall accompany you.

803
00:56:48,750 --> 00:56:49,500
Really?

804
00:56:49,740 --> 00:56:50,440
Yes, Master.

805
00:57:19,050 --> 00:57:21,360
That deadpan-looking lord
says it's dangerous.

806
00:57:22,460 --> 00:57:24,800
It's not dangerous at all. It's gorgeous.

807
00:57:26,440 --> 00:57:29,080
The people here
seem kind and friendly, too.

808
00:57:32,140 --> 00:57:34,440
Where are the bars? I haven't seen any.

809
00:57:35,380 --> 00:57:37,160
This quarter of the market
is most lively, Master.

810
00:57:37,490 --> 00:57:40,480
Taverns and indulgences may be found
only at the mouth of the canal.

811
00:57:41,100 --> 00:57:43,360
There, the place swarms
with foreigners and rogues.

812
00:57:43,790 --> 00:57:45,800
The Lord is doubtless concerned
about that quarter.

813
00:57:48,660 --> 00:57:49,760
Chuay.

814
00:57:50,170 --> 00:57:51,880
Can you help me get to the riverbank?

815
00:57:54,030 --> 00:57:55,280
Oh, Master Klao.

816
00:57:55,800 --> 00:57:57,440
Do not fill my heart with worry,
I beg of you.

817
00:58:00,210 --> 00:58:01,000
Ow!

818
00:58:01,430 --> 00:58:02,400
I'm feeling dizzy

819
00:58:02,990 --> 00:58:03,990
and queasy.

820
00:58:04,200 --> 00:58:05,040
I'm about to pass out.

821
00:58:05,490 --> 00:58:07,800
Take me to the riverbank.

822
00:58:08,250 --> 00:58:10,680
It cannot be done, Master.

823
00:58:10,780 --> 00:58:12,000
This is by the Lord's order.

824
00:58:14,990 --> 00:58:17,560
- Fine. I'll swim there then.
- Uh...

825
00:58:19,780 --> 00:58:21,080
Understood, Master.

826
00:58:21,360 --> 00:58:24,660
Were we to approach the mouth of the canal,
the Lord would punish me severely.

827
00:58:25,450 --> 00:58:26,720
Sure.

828
00:58:27,670 --> 00:58:29,660
Ow! I feel lightheaded again.

829
00:58:29,790 --> 00:58:32,360
- Get me off the boat already!
- Yes, Master.

830
00:58:46,960 --> 00:58:47,960
Do you see, Master?

831
00:58:57,570 --> 00:58:59,040
Master, pray wait.

832
00:59:24,640 --> 00:59:25,600
Master.

833
00:59:28,600 --> 00:59:29,760
Master Klao.

834
00:59:30,440 --> 00:59:31,920
Venture not beyond the pier.

835
00:59:33,870 --> 00:59:34,680
Whoa.

836
00:59:35,150 --> 00:59:36,440
This is so cool.

837
00:59:36,670 --> 00:59:37,700
Master.

838
00:59:39,340 --> 00:59:40,300
Master Klao,

839
00:59:41,160 --> 00:59:43,520
we have strayed too far from the pier.
It is best we return.

840
00:59:44,420 --> 00:59:45,440
Come on, just a little more.

841
00:59:53,800 --> 00:59:54,820
One of these, please.

842
00:59:58,330 --> 00:59:59,760
Let us return
once we have acquired the goods.

843
01:00:06,680 --> 01:00:10,100
- Help! Help me!
- Be wary, my Lady!

844
01:00:10,480 --> 01:00:12,920
I can bear it no more! I beg of you!

845
01:00:14,150 --> 01:00:15,520
Pray, stop this!

846
01:00:16,080 --> 01:00:18,190
- Help me!
- Cease this harassment!

847
01:00:18,220 --> 01:00:19,120
Mind your own affairs!

848
01:00:19,830 --> 01:00:22,440
This matter is none of your concern.

849
01:00:22,700 --> 01:00:24,540
Meddle not, or you shall face my wrath!

850
01:00:27,250 --> 01:00:29,660
- Master. Master Klao!
- Help! Help me!

851
01:00:29,690 --> 01:00:31,480
- Master Klao.
- Out of the way.

852
01:00:32,450 --> 01:00:33,360
Trying to slip away?

853
01:00:33,480 --> 01:00:35,480
You dare escape my reach?!

854
01:00:36,220 --> 01:00:37,120
Hey!

855
01:00:48,550 --> 01:00:49,520
Klao?

856
01:01:00,560 --> 01:01:01,680
You know me?

857
01:01:02,830 --> 01:01:05,040
You. You... You...

858
01:01:29,790 --> 01:01:31,720
Perhaps you are unaware that

859
01:01:31,900 --> 01:01:33,590
you have more adversaries
than you can fathom.

860
01:01:33,630 --> 01:01:34,520
Klao!

861
01:01:34,640 --> 01:01:35,760
Hold thy tongue!

862
01:01:35,820 --> 01:01:37,270
What have you done unto my Brother?!

863
01:01:37,760 --> 01:01:40,080
You don't want me to talk to her
because she's weird?

864
01:01:40,200 --> 01:01:41,320
Tell Chuay

865
01:01:41,640 --> 01:01:42,920
to ready my vessel.

866
01:01:43,190 --> 01:01:43,860
Where to?

867
01:01:44,360 --> 01:01:45,340
To seek the truth.

868
01:01:49,480 --> 01:01:50,880
I do not wish to be parted from you.

869
01:01:50,910 --> 01:01:54,300
♫Stay right here♫

870
01:01:54,340 --> 01:01:57,770
♫I shall spend the time I hold so dearly♫

871
01:01:57,840 --> 01:02:02,180
♫And make the most of it when I see you♫

872
01:02:02,250 --> 01:02:05,360
♫It makes my life so meaningful♫

873
01:02:05,390 --> 01:02:09,000
♫Simply stay right here♫

874
01:02:09,100 --> 01:02:11,630
♫With those eyes I hold so dearly,♫

875
01:02:11,680 --> 01:02:14,460
♫I shall not falter♫

876
01:02:14,530 --> 01:02:19,260
♫With you by my side, we'll walk together♫

877
01:02:20,160 --> 01:02:24,320
♫Forever♫

878
01:02:46,360 --> 01:02:50,470
[Love Upon a Time Series]

